{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AowkSDCdesaUbn7kGLHGqW","type":"tool_result","content":"  3770→## 5. What Went Wrong\n  3771→\n  3772→- **Ralph continued running after sprint completion.** Previous retros documented the same bug: Ralph has no \"sprint complete\" exit condition and keeps spawning no-op sessions. This session's predecessor retro explicitly called this out. The bug persists.\n  3773→- **$219.56 in unattributed costs.** The \"unknown\" bucket is 25.9% of total spend. Without proper attribution, cost optimization is guesswork.\n  3774→- **Verification is 53% of total cost.** While correctness is the point, verify phase costs 15x dev phase — the prompts and evidence-gathering are expensive.\n  3775→- **Redundant npm test runs.** At least 3 subagents ran `npm test` twice when once with proper output capture would suffice.\n  3776→- **5 pre-existing BATS failures.** The `all_tasks_complete` test suite has been broken and unreported/unfixed across multiple sessions.\n  3777→\n  3778→## 6. Lessons Learned\n  3779→\n  3780→### Patterns to Repeat\n  3781→- **Fix bugs in code review, not re-dev.** This session's code reviewers fixed all MEDIUM issues directly via Edit, avoiding costly re-development cycles. This is the right approach for non-architectural issues.\n  3782→- **Minimal subagent tool calls.** Both stories averaged 17.5 tool calls per subagent — lean and efficient.\n  3783→- **Deferring out-of-scope LOW items.** Reviewers correctly identified legacy term cleanup as out-of-scope rather than scope-creeping.\n  3784→\n  3785→### Patterns to Avoid\n  3786→- **Running npm test twice.** Subagents should capture full test output in one run, then filter/grep the captured output.\n  3787→- **Re-reading the same file at different offsets.** harness-run.md was read 5 times in one subagent. A single full read (or two reads: top half + bottom half) would suffice.\n  3788→- **Not killing Ralph when sprint is done.** Every no-op session after completion wastes $2-10 in orchestrator + retro costs.\n  3789→\n  3790→## 7. Action Items\n  3791→\n  3792→| Priority | Action | Owner |\n  3793→|----------|--------|-------|\n  3794→| **P0 — DONE** | Sprint is complete. Stop Ralph. | Human operator |\n  3795→| **P1 — CARRY FORWARD** | Add \"sprint complete\" exit condition to Ralph's main loop. | Developer (next sprint) |\n  3796→| **P1 — CARRY FORWARD** | Attribute the \"unknown\" cost bucket — tag orchestrator/retro calls to session IDs. | Developer (next sprint) |\n  3797→| **P2** | Optimize verification prompts to reduce the 53% verify cost share. | Developer (next sprint) |\n  3798→| **P2** | Fix 5 pre-existing BATS failures in `all_tasks_complete` suite. | Developer (next sprint) |\n  3799→| **P2** | Add subagent guideline: run `npm test` once, capture output, grep from capture. | Developer (next sprint) |\n  3800→| **P3** | Clean up legacy terms (black.box references) in patches/ and templates/. | Developer (next sprint) |\n  3801→\n  3802→## 8. Sprint Completion Summary\n  3803→\n  3804→The codeharness sprint is **fully complete**.\n  3805→\n  3806→- **17 epics**, **74 stories**, **0 failures**\n  3807→- **Total cost:** $849.31 across 6,177 API calls\n  3808→- **Average cost per story:** $3.99\n  3809→- **Test coverage:** 96.85% (4,020 tests)\n  3810→- **Duration:** Multiple sessions across multiple days\n  3811→\n  3812→The project delivered: stack detection (Node.js, Python, Rust), multi-stack support, observability enforcement, Docker integration, verification tiers, autonomous execution via Ralph, and comprehensive documentation — all verified to acceptance criteria.\n  3813→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01A9XPq7LBDxmxSgCKUFxewS","session_id":"c3549884-84b1-49d0-b5ba-29ed204ec9b6","uuid":"57b291df-f155-4acd-8799-24b5e920382f","timestamp":"2026-03-28T12:00:35.228Z"}
